{
    "analysis": "We computed global P95 thresholds per component-KPI using the full series, filtered metric and log rows to the incident window (2024-01-20 21:55:52 → 2024-01-20 22:25:52 UTC), and aggregated anomalies. Key findings: (1) many socket-related KPIs across infrastructure and services (carts-db, session-db, queue-master, rabbitmq, catalogue, orders-db, etc.) were anomalous for the entire window (25/25 points), with earliest exceedances at 2024-01-20T21:58:00Z; (2) rabbitmq and rabbitmq-exporter show persistent anomalies across multiple resources (socket, diskio/mem) beginning 21:58Z; (3) logs show system-wide non-zero log.error_count across many services starting ~21:58Z (global P95 = 0 for many services so any error is flagged), indicating errors were triggered simultaneously across services; (4) traces are unavailable, so localization relies on correlated metric and log signals. From fault-identification rules: multiple services show downstream errors, but the most prominent, persistent anomalous component at the same onset time is rabbitmq (with supporting anomalies in queue-master and rabbitmq-exporter). The concurrent spike in socket KPIs system-wide and queue-master log errors suggests message-broker connectivity/socket issues propagated to services. Earliest correlated anomaly time is 2024-01-20T21:58:00Z. Therefore the most probable root cause is a RabbitMQ (message broker) socket-related failure that began ~21:58Z and caused widespread service errors.",
